==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Particulate
<hw>Par*tic"u*late</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*t⟦icr⟧k"⟦usl⟧*l⟦asl⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the form of a particle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Referring to, or produced by, particles, such as
dust, minute germs, etc.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The smallpox is a <qex>particulate</qex> disease.</q>
<rj><qau>Tyndall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Composed of particles; finely divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>particulate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: particulate
<hw>par*tic"u*late</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*t⟦icr⟧k"⟦usl⟧*l⟦asl⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>Matter composed of particles; -- often used in the
